answersResultList.title: Job success.
answersResultList.resultContent: Success will come if you work for it. Your dream job might be on the other side of a few nightmare gigs, but that's the learning curve. You'll need to make hard choices and maybe a sacrifice or two. Stand up at the right moments and show the right people what you're made of. You're just too good to ignore.

answersResultList.title: New friends.
answersResultList.resultContent: Open your door and broaden your horizons. Some of those strangers out there are destined to be great friends. When you lower your filters of prejudgment, it's miraculous what comes through. Don't pretend to be someone you're not, but definitely put your best qualities on display. Strong friendship grows from total honesty about personal and universal truths.

answersResultList.title: Love.
answersResultList.resultContent: Love will find you. You'll find love. Either way, you'll make it happen. Limit your come-hither vibes to people who are actually good for you, and the story is likely to end happily. Maybe you'll start a family together. Or maybe you will live in a seemingly perpetual honeymoon, traveling and experiencing all the joys of life together. Surrender to the relationship and leave room for pleasant surprises.

answersResultList.title: More money
answersResultList.resultContent: Whether you squeeze the Benjamins until they scream or spend money to make money, you'll end up with more of it. Studying economic theory is fine, but ultimately you have to go with your gut. Just remember, however much you have, it never seems like enough. Material wealth won't make you happy, although it will certainly make life easier.
